text: Kinterbish Creek is a stream in the U.S. states of Alabama and Mississippi. It is a tributary to the Tombigbee River. Kinterbish is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "beaver dam". Variant names are "Abeshai Creek", "Big Kinterbish Creek", "Kintabish Creek", "Kintabush Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Alabama Category:Bodies of water of Choctaw County, Alabama Category:Bodies of water of Sumter County, Alabama Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Lauderdale County, Mississippi
